+      "id": "swiglu-activation",
+      "title": "Replace ReLU-squared with SwiGLU in MLP",
+      "rationale": "SwiGLU (gated SiLU) consistently outperforms ReLU² in transformer language models across scales (Shazeer 2020, LLaMA). The gating mechanism provides smoother gradients and better feature selection. At equal FLOPs the improvement is typically 1-3% in loss. While this adds a gate projection, the inner dimension can be adjusted to keep param count similar.",
+      "risk": "medium",
+      "expectedImpact": "medium",
+      "changes": "In train.py MLP class: add a gate linear c_gate = nn.Linear(n_embd, 4*n_embd, bias=False). In forward(), compute gate = F.silu(self.c_gate(x)) and up = self.c_fc(x), then x = gate * up before c_proj. Update init_weights to initialize c_gate with the same uniform distribution as c_fc. The 4x inner dim is kept (slight param increase) for simplicity; reducing to 8/3*n_embd is an optional follow-up.",
